        <num>CCP 3062</num>
        <heading>3062.  Effect of judgment of possession</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3062.  Effect of judgment of possession
The judgment of possession rendered in a succession proceeding shall be prima facie evidence of the relationship to the deceased of the parties recognized therein, as heir, legatee, surviving spouse in community, or usufructuary, as the case may be, and of their right to the possession of the estate of the deceased.</p>
        </content>
